To Thomas and Richard,=0A=
=0A=
I have a question regarding certain finite limit preserving functors Set-->=
Set.=0A=
=0A=
If L is a locale, then the functor Hom(L,-):Set-->Set preserves finite limi=
ts, =0A=
where  Hom(L,X) denotes the set of  morphisms of locales L-->X for a discre=
te locale X. =0A=
Is there is a simple characterization of these flp functors?=0A=
=0A=
Best,=0A=
Andr=E9=0A=
=0A=
