Dear Richard,=0A=
=0A=
thanks for your answer. Offline I have received a reply by Jonas Frey=0A=
which answers my question satisfactorily.=0A=
Let U be a Groth. universe then Lex(U,Set) consists of filtered/directed=0A=
colimits of representables. Accordingly, Lex(U,U) is equivalent to the=0A=
full subcat of Set^U on U-small directed colimits of representables.=0A=
=0A=
But that sounds related to what Blass says, isn't it.=0A=
=0A=
Best, Thomas=0A=
